Staffers of Henkel Nigeria have used the opportunity of the United Nations International Volunteering Day to visit two orphanages in Ibadan, Oyo State – His Heritage Home and Tabitha Home.
 
The visits were in line with the firm’s recognition and support of voluntary employee engagement in its host communities. Detergents, food materials, groceries and stationeries were donated to the children’s homes.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .